"559","<TEXT>"
"560","AMENDMENT TO BY-LAWS OF"
"561","THE STRATTON FUNDS, INC."
"562","      Pursuant to Section 2-109(b) of the Maryland General"
"563","Corporation Law and Article IX of the By-Laws of The"
"564","Stratton Funds, Inc. (the Corporation), effective"
"565","September 27, 2011, the By-Laws of the Corporation shall be"
"566","amended as follows:"
"567","Article VII, Section 1, Section 2 and Section 4 shall be"
"568","deleted in their entirety."
"569","Article VII, Section 3 shall be titled Section 1 and"
"570","shall be amended and restated in its entirety as follows:"
"571","      Section 1. Recording and Transfer without Certificates."
"572","The Corporation shall have the full power to participate in"
"573","any program providing for the recording and transfer of"
"574","ownership of shares of the Corporation's stock by electronic"
"575","or other means without the issuance of certificates."
"576","      Article VII, Section 5 and Section 6 shall be titled"
"577","Section 2 and Section 3, respectively."
"578","      Article VII, Section 7 shall be titled Section 4 and"
"579","shall be amended and restated in its entirety as follows:"
"580","      Section 4. Transfer Agents and Registrars. The Board of"
"581","Directors may, from time to time, appoint or remove transfer"
"582","agents and or registrars of the Corporation, and they may"
"583","appoint the same person as both transfer agent and registrar."
"584","      Article VII, Section 8 shall be titled Section 5."
"585","      The foregoing amendments to the By-Laws of the Corporation"
"586","were duly approved by resolution of the Board of Directors at a"
"587","meeting held on September 27, 2011."
"588","</TEXT>"
"589","</DOCUMENT>"
"590","</SEC-DOCUMENT>"
